00:04:09.920 --> 00:04:12.790
online, in person, or both.

00:04:12.790 --> 00:04:18.410
Federation, for those of you who may not know,
was created 100 years ago to solve the most

00:04:18.410 --> 00:04:25.180
significant Jewish challenge of the day. Then,
in 1910, it was a massive immigration of thousands

00:04:25.180 --> 00:04:30.990
of Jews with five dollars or less in their
pockets; my great grandfather included.

00:04:30.990 --> 00:04:37.720
There were brand new social welfare organizations
and the need for very significant fund raising,

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:42.150
collaboration, and organization for the community
as a whole.

00:04:42.150 --> 00:04:48.020
In 1910, remember, Jews had never been fully
accepted in any society; never completely

00:04:48.020 --> 00:04:54.900
safe anywhere they landed. By then, it had
become very clear that we are stronger when

00:04:54.900 --> 00:05:01.120
we are organized and that we need to care
for our own anywhere that they may be.

00:05:01.120 --> 00:05:07.180
Couple that with the Torah's 32 references
to the Mitzvah of Tzedakah, social justice,

00:05:07.180 --> 00:05:12.340
and the 18th century rabbinic convention of
Tikkun Olam, the imperative to repair not

00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:17.840
just the Jewish world but the broader world
in which we live and these became the pillars

00:05:17.840 --> 00:05:23.870
of the Federation; solving big challenges
and working as a community foundation to strengthen

00:05:23.870 --> 00:05:25.160
community.

00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:31.610
Year after year, decade after decade, enormous
issues continued to face the Jewish community

00:05:31.610 --> 00:05:37.889
as well as the rest of the world and Federation
was always and continues to be the first responder.

00:05:37.889 --> 00:05:43.180
We have always been there to make sure the
community is safe, strong, vibrant, including

00:05:43.180 --> 00:05:49.020
through two world wars, The Great Depression,
the Holocaust, Israel's independence and five

00:05:49.020 --> 00:05:52.880
wars, and ongoing terrorist threats through
today.

00:05:52.880 --> 00:05:58.240
Beginning in the 1970s the Bay Area community
took on the human rights and immigration issues

00:05:58.240 --> 00:06:04.330
of Soviet Jews, and after years and years
of local sit-ins, demonstrations, trips to

00:06:04.330 --> 00:06:10.370
the former Soviet Union, and a campaign locally
that raised 29 million dollars in support

00:06:10.370 --> 00:06:16.449
of a one billion dollar national effort, Natan's
dream and the dream of a million Soviet Jews

00:06:16.449 --> 00:06:22.800
was realized to leave the former Soviet Union
and to live freely and openly without fear,

00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:26.389
hunger, imprisonment, or injury.

00:06:26.389 --> 00:06:31.350
This year in addition to celebrating our 100th
anniversary, we celebrate the 20th anniversary

00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:36.139
of this incredible rescue and relocation effort;
one that involved so many of this community's

00:06:36.139 --> 00:06:37.330
leaders very intimately.

00:06:37.330 --> 00:06:43.520
Throughout these many years, Federation, in
its dual role as the ongoing philanthropic

00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:50.789
engine for vibrant Jewish life and a caring
community, has done this in two ways.

00:06:50.789 --> 00:06:56.360
First, raising over 20 million dollars annually
to invest in the community to strengthen Jewish

00:06:56.360 --> 00:07:02.240
life here, in Israel, and around the world,
and also through the Center of Philanthropy,

00:07:02.240 --> 00:07:05.169
which I'll talk about in just a moment.

00:07:05.169 --> 00:07:10.830
Annually we invest in specific portfolios:
First Engagement. We open as many doors as

00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:17.020
possible to Jewish living, remove as many
barriers to access including those that make

00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:22.919
Jewish life not affordable for many people,
and focus on youth education and young adult

00:07:22.919 --> 00:07:24.720
philanthropy.

00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:29.569
For example, a few years ago, we made our
largest endowment gift of 10 million dollars

00:07:29.569 --> 00:07:33.509
to build the local Taube Koret Campus for
Jewish Life.

00:07:33.509 --> 00:07:38.539
In the last year alone, we granted more than
1.6 million dollars in scholarships for our

00:07:38.539 --> 00:07:40.720
day schools and camps.

00:07:40.720 --> 00:07:45.900
And we have just launched a venture style
philanthropy initiative in which 21 to 45

00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:51.919
year olds will connect with each other to
select among their peers the very best models

00:07:51.919 --> 00:07:57.449
of innovative Jewish living. This sector,
the key ingredient for Jewish connections

00:07:57.449 --> 00:08:02.990
and continuity, garnered an investment from
us of about 10 million dollars of annual funds

00:08:02.990 --> 00:08:05.050
this year.

00:08:05.050 --> 00:08:08.259
Second, Israel and overseas.

00:08:08.259 --> 00:08:12.569
There we strengthened Democracy in Israel,
build bridges during a time of increasing

00:08:12.569 --> 00:08:16.479
isolation, and care for Jews everywhere around
the world.

00:08:16.479 --> 00:08:21.580
This is a time not to shy away from Israel's
complex issues, but to educate ourselves and

00:08:21.580 --> 00:08:28.889
to find ways to help. We do this work by making
it possible to send as many kids as we can

00:08:28.889 --> 00:08:34.110
on birthright trips; these are free trips
for young adults to Israel.

00:08:34.110 --> 00:08:39.760
By populating all of our Northern California
college campus-campuses with Shalichim, that

00:08:39.760 --> 00:08:47.060
is young adults who come from Natan's organization,
Jafi, to work through our Hillels and by funding

00:08:47.060 --> 00:08:52.260
disadvantaged youth and elderly in Israel.

00:08:52.260 --> 00:09:02.120
We also work on pluralism by creating leaders
in Israel who will strengthen tolerance in

00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:08.920
Israeli society. This sector garnered an investment
last year of more than 4.3 million dollars.

00:09:08.920 --> 00:09:15.670
And finally, our third sector, creating a
caring community of Jews especially for those

00:09:15.670 --> 00:09:21.310
who would be virtually invisible; those Jews
who live in poverty in the Bay Area, the former

00:09:21.310 --> 00:09:27.180
Soviet Union, and in Israel; single parent
families, children with special needs, and

00:09:27.180 --> 00:09:34.279
the elderly poor. In this sector, we also
invested 4.3 million dollars this year.

00:09:34.279 --> 00:09:38.740
And second, as I mentioned earlier, we are
really a center of philanthropy providing

00:09:38.740 --> 00:09:44.300
donor involved solutions that are tax efficient;
provide great investments; and provide a staff

00:09:44.300 --> 00:09:50.510
of experts to advise on the philanthropic
vision, mission, and values of each donor

00:09:50.510 --> 00:09:55.860
and to research the world's charities so that
we can facilitate philanthropy to any public

00:09:55.860 --> 00:09:58.080
charity one could imagine.

00:09:58.080 --> 00:10:03.450
We appreciate that in this era of globalization
and nearly complete Jewish integration, our

00:10:03.450 --> 00:10:08.550
efforts to help anyone, anywhere in the world
are just as much our imperative as insuring

00:10:08.550 --> 00:10:11.120
that the Jewish community is strong.

00:10:11.120 --> 00:10:16.890
The JCF enables the individual to leverage
his or her own dollars for good through collaboration

00:10:16.890 --> 00:10:22.700
with us, with other funders, and with networks;
the leverage that comes from acting as an

00:10:22.700 --> 00:10:24.410
interconnected group.

00:10:24.410 --> 00:10:31.140
The Jews as a people have always seen themselves
as a global people through time and space

00:10:31.140 --> 00:10:37.760
just as many philanthropists have come to
view themselves as global in their orientation

00:10:37.760 --> 00:10:39.700
through time and space.

00:10:39.700 --> 00:10:46.180
And so the Federation, as a community foundation,
construe the world in this way too. As a connector,

00:10:46.180 --> 00:10:51.750
a convener, a collaborator, and a leveraging
resource, we really do have something in common

00:10:51.750 --> 00:10:52.750
with Google.

00:10:52.750 --> 00:10:55.970
I know it's a stretch, but we're trying.

00:10:55.970 --> 00:10:56.970
[laughter]

00:10:56.970 --> 00:11:01.530
The message of the Federation is that each
and every one of us plays a vital role in

00:11:01.530 --> 00:11:06.610
a collective that has the power to have enormous
impact on our community and on our world.

00:11:06.610 --> 00:11:13.079
In our own individual ways, acting on our
own values, thinking creatively, strategically,

00:11:13.079 --> 00:11:18.380
and generously through an annual community
investment, through a donor advised fund,

00:11:18.380 --> 00:11:26.029
or through an endowed fund, we are part of
a powerful and generous interconnected community

00:11:26.029 --> 00:11:31.450
We are all in this together to save lives,
to improve lives, and to transform lives.

00:11:31.450 --> 00:11:37.149
That's the power of our Federation community;
one that manages and stewards over one billion

00:11:37.149 --> 00:11:43.360
dollars of assets and last year granted more
than 154 million dollars all over the world

00:11:43.360 --> 00:11:49.550
from our annual fund, our 900 plus donor advised
funds, and our 70 foundations and endowed

00:11:49.550 --> 00:11:50.550
funds.

00:11:50.550 --> 00:11:57.600
A thriving community needs many things: great
vision, financial investment, builders, sustainers,

00:11:57.600 --> 00:12:00.680
a thick web of connection, and heart.

00:12:00.680 --> 00:12:06.120
We are here to make sure that all of these
ingredients come together for joy, for meaning,

00:12:06.120 --> 00:12:10.490
for family, for continuity from generation
to generation.

00:12:10.490 --> 00:12:17.070
Please join me in welcoming Natan Sharansky,
our featured speaker today.

00:12:17.070 --> 00:12:18.740
[applause]

00:12:18.740 --> 00:12:22.380
&gt;&gt;Natan Sharansky: Thank you.

00:12:22.380 --> 00:12:28.829
Well I'm very glad to be here and thank you
for my introduction where it was said that

00:12:28.829 --> 00:12:33.720
we have something in common that I was implied
in the semantics that we follow with this

00:12:33.720 --> 00:12:34.720
parallel.

00:12:34.720 --> 00:12:43.910
In fact it was a more powerful parallel because
I, when I, when I was a school child in Soviet

00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:49.500
Union the first Soviet computers appeared;
it was in the 60s.

00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:57.560
And the first computer that I was working
on was doing one hundred operations per second;

00:12:57.560 --> 00:13:07.100
it was all on, built on radio bulbs; it was
before transistors; so these bulbs, so in

00:13:07.100 --> 00:13:11.899
fact the speed of the computer was defined
with the speed with which you can replace

00:13:11.899 --> 00:13:14.430
the bulbs because they were broken all the
time.

00:13:14.430 --> 00:13:15.430
[laughter]

00:13:15.430 --> 00:13:21.529
And with this technology, then I went to one
of a very prestigious Soviet university became

00:13:21.529 --> 00:13:28.630
a special in the department of medicine as
it was in my master degree that I invented

00:13:28.630 --> 00:13:36.550
the first chess program, computer program
to play chess – Anspiel files; the Anspiel

00:13:36.550 --> 00:13:37.610
chess games.

00:13:37.610 --> 00:13:42.660
It was then the first attempts of writing
such programs and Anspiel was especial difficult

00:13:42.660 --> 00:13:51.261
because well the all the al-algorithms then
were based on your analyzing the tree of all

00:13:51.261 --> 00:14:00.190
possible developments and then you compare
them, or you have to count up to them, what

00:14:00.190 --> 00:14:05.270
was then simply impossible or you have to
have some kind of comparison based on some

00:14:05.270 --> 00:14:11.500
criterias. And at the end of the game, those
who know chess it is, was especially difficult.

00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:18.120
And so I created the semantical program which
was dealing with artificial intellect which

00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:24.949
tried not only to have formal comparison but
tried to have some logical the battle; how

00:14:24.949 --> 00:14:29.800
you building strategy; go from the beginning
to the end then you go from the end to the

00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:33.610
beginning and then again I will not into the
details, but really I tried to simulate the

00:14:33.610 --> 00:14:36.460
building of the strategy by in a, in a logical
way.

00:14:36.460 --> 00:14:39.840
And I was very proud of it. It was written
on the first time you have this end game.

00:14:39.840 --> 00:14:46.519
And then I was arrested and I spent nine years
in prison and when I was released though I

00:14:46.519 --> 00:14:51.360
while in prison and punishing and in solitary
confinement, I had a lot of experience of

00:14:51.360 --> 00:14:55.640
playing chess in my head with myself and I
won all these games --

00:14:55.640 --> 00:14:56.640
[laughter]

00:14:56.640 --> 00:15:02.850
but here I didn't an ability to improve my
what was computer program so though, after

00:15:02.850 --> 00:15:07.750
nine years that I was in prison, four generations
of computers were born and died.

00:15:07.750 --> 00:15:15.240
So I went into the absolute new world; it
was just, there were personal computers, it

00:15:15.240 --> 00:15:18.180
was absolute different there. So I assumed
there was no way that I can compete and all

00:15:18.180 --> 00:15:24.839
my powerful program already had no meaning
because it appeared a few years after this

00:15:24.839 --> 00:15:31.139
real powerful search engines like Google which
denied all what I was doing. In fact they

00:15:31.139 --> 00:15:33.630
simply ignored all this. [chuckles]

00:15:33.630 --> 00:15:34.630
[laughter]

00:15:34.630 --> 00:15:38.390
And-and so I decided there is, that I really
have to change my profession so I didn't go

00:15:38.390 --> 00:15:44.250
back [ ] and simply enjoying them as a client
of Google and these great things that you

00:15:44.250 --> 00:15:46.279
are doing.

00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:49.910
Now the second thing which I wanted to say
and I am glad that it was said in the beginning,

00:15:49.910 --> 00:15:57.610
in fact I was very pleased, I tried to send
my personal appreciation to the head of Google

00:15:57.610 --> 00:16:03.180
who worked for the position that you took
in China. Because the one who spent a lot

00:16:03.180 --> 00:16:09.580
of years in struggling for freedom and democracy
and then in the last years trying to build

00:16:09.580 --> 00:16:13.970
international support of democratic dissidents
all over the world.

00:16:13.970 --> 00:16:19.060
I organized big international conference of
democratic dissidents you will see Garry Kasparov

00:16:19.060 --> 00:16:26.199
just saw one of my good friends, but people
like him acting in China, in Egypt, in Syria,

00:16:26.199 --> 00:16:32.279
and many other countries. And I know from
my experience and their experience how international

00:16:32.279 --> 00:16:39.740
solidarity is important and how betraying
is the behavior of those people in the free

00:16:39.740 --> 00:16:44.079
world who are ready to cooperate with all
the dictators of the world only to have their

00:16:44.079 --> 00:16:48.440
business. And all those explanations if you
will not do it, somebody else will do it.

00:16:48.440 --> 00:16:50.740
And about China, I've heard it from many businessmen.

00:16:50.740 --> 00:16:56.970
And it was also very upsetting to see how
this great weapon of freedom which was invented.

00:16:56.970 --> 00:17:01.320
In our times when we were dissidents in the
former Soviet Union there were no CNN and

00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:11.110
no Internet and it was so easy to authorities
to cut us from all the world. It was so difficult

00:17:11.110 --> 00:17:18.010
to bring information to the, to the citizens
of the Soviet Union which we were doing through

00:17:18.010 --> 00:17:23.510
in a very difficult ways through foreign radio
stations by risking the lives of many people.

00:17:23.510 --> 00:17:28.300
And here we have Internet; here we have such
powerful weapon and which is used if you know

00:17:28.300 --> 00:17:31.039
Iranian dissidents it was one of their main
weapons.

00:17:31.039 --> 00:17:39.210
So and then this Internet is used by secret
police to dis, to-to discover their political

00:17:39.210 --> 00:17:44.210
opinions and to repress them. That was very
painful and disappointing. And so I'm very

00:17:44.210 --> 00:17:53.010
glad that Google became pioneer in this field
and I can only hope that in spite of many,

00:17:53.010 --> 00:18:01.430
many business, businessmen who think that-that
making business is the best contribution to

00:18:01.430 --> 00:18:06.230
peace and that well let's ignore all this
moral restrictions that in fact the example

00:18:06.230 --> 00:18:12.500
Google will be broadened, supported, and that's
something extremely important. And for this

00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:19.610
you-you deserve a lot of credit in addition
to the fact that you invented search engine

00:18:19.610 --> 00:18:24.070
which destroyed all my theories which I was
building before --

00:18:24.070 --> 00:18:25.070
[laughter]

00:18:25.070 --> 00:18:26.140
I went to prison.

00:18:26.140 --> 00:18:27.140
Okay.

