00:19:04.120 --> 00:19:09.919
was controlling one-third of the earth; physically
it was a regime which controlled 200 million

00:19:09.919 --> 00:19:14.490
people of the, citizens of the former Soviet
Union.

00:19:14.490 --> 00:19:22.190
And it was controlling not only their-their
physical life, but their minds. In fact, the

00:19:22.190 --> 00:19:27.270
regime which ideologically in the beginning
of the 20th century came with idea that now

00:19:27.270 --> 00:19:32.910
we are creating society of equal people, that
everybody's equal; there is no exploitation

00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:37.230
of one or the other. But in order they will
be absolutely, completely equal there should

00:19:37.230 --> 00:19:41.090
be no differences. And that's why they should
have no property; all the property will be

00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:44.750
taken by the State and State will decide how
to distribute the property.

00:19:44.750 --> 00:19:52.230
And there will no national or religious differences.
And that's why we will destroy nationalism;

00:19:52.230 --> 00:19:58.549
we will destroy religion. Everybody has to
be loyal to our idea-ideology and not to anything

00:19:58.549 --> 00:19:59.549
else.

00:19:59.549 --> 00:20:04.290
And because the nature of the people was resistant
to this, so they in the beginning as Lenin

00:20:04.290 --> 00:20:11.340
wrote, if you will have to kill bunch of capitalists
who are preventing us from having society

00:20:11.340 --> 00:20:15.070
where everybody will be equal, so we will
have to kill them.

00:20:15.070 --> 00:20:18.559
So they start killing from hundreds and then
thousands, and tens of thousands, hundreds

00:20:18.559 --> 00:20:20.419
of thousands, tens-tens of millions.

00:20:20.419 --> 00:20:26.770
Then now historians are discussing whether
the number of victims of this regime of their

00:20:26.770 --> 00:20:32.600
own citizens was 20 million or 30 million
or 40 million; so really even difficult to-to

00:20:32.600 --> 00:20:33.600
appreciate.

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:38.600
But that was the result of this attempt to
create society where there is no, everybody's

00:20:38.600 --> 00:20:39.679
equal.

00:20:39.679 --> 00:20:46.020
As a result I am, I was already the second
if not the third generation of absolutely

00:20:46.020 --> 00:20:52.830
assimilated Soviet Jews. And when I was assimilated,
I lived in the big city in the Ukraine with

00:20:52.830 --> 00:20:58.950
half a million population with at least 50,000
Jews and they knew nothing about my history,

00:20:58.950 --> 00:21:02.960
about my holidays, about my tradition, about
anything.

00:21:02.960 --> 00:21:07.200
More than this, I was born few years after
Holocaust in the places where hundreds of

00:21:07.200 --> 00:21:13.679
thousands of my people and also many of my
relatives were killed and we grew knowing

00:21:13.679 --> 00:21:18.640
nothing about Holocaust. We knew of course
about great victory of Soviet Union over Hitler,

00:21:18.640 --> 00:21:25.140
but the fact that there were millions killed
only for being Jewish, we didn't know. It

00:21:25.140 --> 00:21:32.059
was deprived from our knowledge; it was deliberately
done in order not to do anything which can

00:21:32.059 --> 00:21:40.560
give us kind of all national pride, all national
desire or whatever.

00:21:40.560 --> 00:21:44.020
And the same time we knew where it was that
we were Jewish, why? Because it is written

00:21:44.020 --> 00:21:47.980
in the idea of your parents and there is a
lot of anti-Semitism; lot of restrictions;

00:21:47.980 --> 00:21:53.179
all the discussion told us what is possible
not what was not possible to do.

00:21:53.179 --> 00:22:00.059
And as a result, the message which we are
getting from our parents is that because you

00:22:00.059 --> 00:22:07.840
are Jews, you must be the best in physics
or in the semantics or in chess or in music,

00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:12.530
it doesn't matter in what. But you must be
the best in your profession. That's why, that's

00:22:12.530 --> 00:22:20.670
you can go to this tower of science or what
and maybe then you'll be protected as Jews;

00:22:20.670 --> 00:22:22.720
maybe you'll suffer less.

00:22:22.720 --> 00:22:31.320
And that was the idea how to survive, to become
good specialists and how to survive.

00:22:31.320 --> 00:22:36.460
And then we totally were deprived of identity,
but we also were deprived of freedom. It was

00:22:36.460 --> 00:22:40.309
clear for us from our childhood that we live
under dictatorship.

00:22:40.309 --> 00:22:45.720
The, I always tell the story when I became
loyal citizen simply-simply because it's,

00:22:45.720 --> 00:22:52.400
shows in one short story, it shows immediately
what was the state of mind of Soviet people.

00:22:52.400 --> 00:22:59.420
I was five years old when Stalin died. Though
you are young, but probably you know who was

00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:00.420
Stalin.

00:23:00.420 --> 00:23:04.930
And so when Stalin died, I came home from
kindergarten and my, and we lived then in

00:23:04.930 --> 00:23:10.950
communal apartment: three, four, five families
in one apartment with one kitchen, with one

00:23:10.950 --> 00:23:11.950
toilet, and so on.

00:23:11.950 --> 00:23:20.010
And father making sure that neighbors don't
hear told me that Stalin was awful man; he

00:23:20.010 --> 00:23:25.970
killed a lot of people; we Jews we are in
big danger, but now we are saved and I should

00:23:25.970 --> 00:23:30.900
remember all my life that miracle happened,
Stalin died. But he said don't tell it to

00:23:30.900 --> 00:23:36.190
anybody. Do what everybody does and next day
go to kindergarten and there in the kindergarten

00:23:36.190 --> 00:23:42.710
I cried together with all children because
Stalin died and I sing song how grateful we

00:23:42.710 --> 00:23:47.480
are to the great leader of all the people,
Stalin, who gave us such a happy childhood

00:23:47.480 --> 00:23:49.210
that was the [ ] of the song.

00:23:49.210 --> 00:23:54.420
So I sing it; I cry; and I remember miracle
happened I should be very happy Stalin died.

00:23:54.420 --> 00:23:55.420
[laughter]

00:23:55.420 --> 00:24:02.230
That is typical state of mind of loyal Soviet
citizen. It's double think. You don't believe

00:24:02.230 --> 00:24:10.110
in this regime and with time every dictator
in the regime as I later tried to show in

00:24:10.110 --> 00:24:13.670
my books every dictatorial regime the number
of double thinkers is growing with the time.

00:24:13.670 --> 00:24:20.070
So they are not already true believers they
are double thinkers, but they're not dissidents.

00:24:20.070 --> 00:24:25.029
Because dissidents are those who are crossing
this line and who are ready to risk their

00:24:25.029 --> 00:24:26.029
life.

00:24:26.029 --> 00:24:30.410
But to think that people cross this line and
would become dissidents, what, why to risk

00:24:30.410 --> 00:24:35.150
a life; there is no value in this life. The
only value is how to survive; how to become

00:24:35.150 --> 00:24:38.159
good specialists and then work in your ivory
tower and that's it. And of course you feel

00:24:38.159 --> 00:24:45.370
yourself very uncomfortable; you don't have
any strength to fight against it.

00:24:45.370 --> 00:24:52.850
So I was deprived of freedom, and over identity.
And I had no force to struggle for anything.

00:24:52.850 --> 00:24:58.159
When it all changed. Two events happened,
very important.

00:24:58.159 --> 00:25:04.950
One was in 1967 Israel emerged victorious
against its neighbors who wanted to destroy

00:25:04.950 --> 00:25:09.410
Israel. And for Soviet Union, that was a very
big humiliation, very big humiliation. And

00:25:09.410 --> 00:25:14.720
because Soviet Union sent a lot of money and
lot of soldiers in fact, a lot of weapons

00:25:14.720 --> 00:25:20.840
to Syria to, and to Egypt and already started
celebrating the victory.

00:25:20.840 --> 00:25:29.299
And so suddenly, it's all changed and you
see how for the people around you they are

00:25:29.299 --> 00:25:33.090
changing their attitude to you; those who
like you, those who hate you.

00:25:33.090 --> 00:25:38.740
But they connected with Israel that even anti-Semitic
jokes and there was every day, there was another

00:25:38.740 --> 00:25:42.740
anti-Semitic joke there about different Jews.
Yesterday they were about Jews who are cowards

00:25:42.740 --> 00:25:47.600
and who want to take money off somebody. Today
they are about Jews who are hooligans, who

00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:50.280
are fighting, who are beating the others.

00:25:50.280 --> 00:25:55.150
So you understand that for these people somehow,
you're connected to Israel and you want to

00:25:55.150 --> 00:25:59.570
understand this connection. And you start
reading in the underground because there is

00:25:59.570 --> 00:26:08.050
no way to read it publicly. From the books
which are brought mainly by tourists, American

00:26:08.050 --> 00:26:10.380
Jews and not only American -- tourists.

00:26:10.380 --> 00:26:15.961
And you discover there is great history which
starts from exodus from Egypt and it's so

00:26:15.961 --> 00:26:20.830
easy to feel yourself part of that exodus
and which continues with the Exodus of Leon

00:26:20.830 --> 00:26:26.820
Uris. And Leon Uris, if you read today it's
Bubba Meisah. It's interesting but whether

00:26:26.820 --> 00:26:28.289
it's true or not.

00:26:28.289 --> 00:26:34.210
But then it was such a powerful discovery
that people of our age can be part of this

00:26:34.210 --> 00:26:35.400
great history.

00:26:35.400 --> 00:26:40.610
And so suddenly discover this great history
and you discover there are Jews who are all

00:26:40.610 --> 00:26:46.059
over world who feel solidarity with you. And
you feel stronger; you want to part of this

00:26:46.059 --> 00:26:51.420
history. And that what starts giving you this
feeling that there are things more important

00:26:51.420 --> 00:26:57.370
than your physical survival. And that what
will, what will become the big source of strength

00:26:57.370 --> 00:27:02.120
for me to fight for my rights, for rights
of other Jews, and for the rights of many

00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:03.120
non-Jews.

00:27:03.120 --> 00:27:09.289
And there was another important event. Another
important event is the letter -- Andrei Sokolov.

00:27:09.289 --> 00:27:15.550
Andrei Sokolov who at the time became a great
friend, my great leader, I would say my great

00:27:15.550 --> 00:27:20.640
rabbi but he was not Jewish so he could not
be rabbi.

00:27:20.640 --> 00:27:21.640
[laughter]

00:27:21.640 --> 00:27:26.740
But-but that is, that was scientist number
one of the Soviet Union. There was nobody

00:27:26.740 --> 00:27:36.010
even close to him. He was the father of hydrogen
bomb; he was the great, made great discoveries

00:27:36.010 --> 00:27:42.210
in theoretical and experimental physics. From
the age of 29 he not only was the member of

00:27:42.210 --> 00:27:47.870
academia but he had all the top Soviet awards.
There was nobody even close in com-compared

00:27:47.870 --> 00:27:48.870
to him.

00:27:48.870 --> 00:27:50.880
And this man ?

00:27:50.880 --> 00:27:52.420
[pause]

00:27:52.420 --> 00:27:59.130
published a letter; in-- it was 1968. Published
a letter to the Soviet leaders where he writes

00:27:59.130 --> 00:28:05.919
that if Soviet leaders will not permit freedom
of thought for their citizens there is no

00:28:05.919 --> 00:28:11.161
chance that Soviet Union will be a superpower;
because the best physics in the world, the

00:28:11.161 --> 00:28:17.750
best mathematics in the world, the best talents,
but it-it will mean nothing if you're not

00:28:17.750 --> 00:28:22.200
giving the freedom of discussion, the freedom
of thought to-to our citizens.

00:28:22.200 --> 00:28:29.700
Of course they immediately changed his status;
he immediately became a dissident and he lost

00:28:29.700 --> 00:28:32.250
all his privilege in this society.

00:28:32.250 --> 00:28:38.220
But what it meant for me, I thought, "Look
I am trying to find the way into this castle

00:28:38.220 --> 00:28:45.549
of science as a young scientist with my funny
programs in chess and in computers and I hope

00:28:45.549 --> 00:28:51.480
to find the piece to my course." Here is a
person who's already on the top. He is at

00:28:51.480 --> 00:28:56.799
the top of this ivory tower; nobody can be
higher than him.

00:28:56.799 --> 00:29:02.860
And he feel that he cannot continue this life
of double think that we all have. That he

00:29:02.860 --> 00:29:07.710
has to say the truth and he has to demand
the truth. And so that had tremendously powerful

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:13.890
influence on me. I understood that all these
attempts to find peace of mind by hiding in

00:29:13.890 --> 00:29:15.280
the world of science impossible.

00:29:15.280 --> 00:29:22.490
So on one hand, this understanding that it
is impossible to adjust yourself because you

00:29:22.490 --> 00:29:28.200
have freedom of thought, and freedom of consciousness,
freedom of will. On the other hand, I discovered

00:29:28.200 --> 00:29:32.860
my identity which gives me a lot of strength;
the strength to start fighting.

00:29:32.860 --> 00:29:37.409
In the beginning all if I did was say publicly,
"I really don't want to live in this country

00:29:37.409 --> 00:29:43.630
I want to leave this country." But that's,
that's -- the moment you said it you already

00:29:43.630 --> 00:29:49.590
crossed the line. You're-you're apart, you
will lose your job, your apartment will be

00:29:49.590 --> 00:29:55.120
searched, your, you will be called for interrogations,
many of your friends will ask you to take

00:29:55.120 --> 00:29:59.260
their names from your telephone book because
they don't want to be, to have problems with

00:29:59.260 --> 00:30:00.890
the secret police.

00:30:00.890 --> 00:30:07.340
But you, but from this moment you stop having
this double life, double life which you started

00:30:07.340 --> 00:30:11.380
in the age of five from the death of Stalin
and which you continue to this day.

00:30:11.380 --> 00:30:16.520
And then you-you have enough strength to start
fighting for your right to immigrate and then

00:30:16.520 --> 00:30:18.370
for the rights of the other people.

00:30:18.370 --> 00:30:25.910
It's a moment I became the unofficial spokesman
of two movements: Soviet Jewry Movement and

00:30:25.910 --> 00:30:30.240
human rights movement of the Soviet Union;
and was very actively working with Andrei

00:30:30.240 --> 00:30:32.250
Sokolov and the other dissidents.

00:30:32.250 --> 00:30:38.210
And at the same time I was very active in
the struggle of Soviet Jews to leave as Jews

00:30:38.210 --> 00:30:40.440
and to go to Israel or to other places.

00:30:40.440 --> 00:30:47.340
And I got to say that I remember there were
people on both sides who were telling me that

00:30:47.340 --> 00:30:53.770
I cannot continue in this. That you really
have to choose or you are Nationalist or you

00:30:53.770 --> 00:30:59.470
are Universalist, or you are for the rights
of that small tribe, small family which is

00:30:59.470 --> 00:31:03.630
called Jews, or you are for the human rights
of all the world.

00:31:03.630 --> 00:31:10.090
And I have to say I-I never felt that I have
to choose. Not only because I enjoyed being

00:31:10.090 --> 00:31:15.130
in both of these movements, I really enjoyed
fighting the regime being in both these movement.

00:31:15.130 --> 00:31:16.130
[laughter]

00:31:16.130 --> 00:31:22.399
But-but because I felt there is deep connection;
that in order you have the strength to fight

00:31:22.399 --> 00:31:28.669
for freedom of all the mankind, you must have
things which are more important for you than

00:31:28.669 --> 00:31:30.070
your physical survival.

00:31:30.070 --> 00:31:38.320
You must have your identity; your desire to
belong is -- that is the source of power to-to

00:31:38.320 --> 00:31:39.919
meet your desire to-to be free.

00:31:39.919 --> 00:31:45.269
And I believe these are two basic desires
of people: to belong and to be free. And only

00:31:45.269 --> 00:31:48.519
when they are connected together you can have
great results.

00:31:48.519 --> 00:31:54.750
And this, from this point, our experience
was to some extent opposite to experience

00:31:54.750 --> 00:31:59.080
of our grandfathers of those of our grandfathers
who joined Communist Revolution. Because what

00:31:59.080 --> 00:32:05.840
was the idea of Communist Revolution? The
idea of them many Jews decided at that moment

00:32:05.840 --> 00:32:14.010
finally we don't have to think only about
our small tribe; about our shtetl. We can

00:32:14.010 --> 00:32:19.460
finally fight with a great ideal of equality
and freedom for all the world; the big people

00:32:19.460 --> 00:32:20.460
of humanity.

00:32:20.460 --> 00:32:27.360
And those who believed in it they helped to
create one of the most awful regimes in-in

00:32:27.360 --> 00:32:31.649
the history which killed tens of millions
of its citizens including all those naive

00:32:31.649 --> 00:32:34.179
idealists who joined the Revolution.

00:32:34.179 --> 00:32:40.360
For this one to be, went in the opposite direction.
We went back to our schtetl, to our tribe,

00:32:40.360 --> 00:32:47.610
to our people, to our language, to our history.
And there we found strength to fight for the,

00:32:47.610 --> 00:32:49.059
for the better for all the world.

00:32:49.059 --> 00:32:56.769
I can tell you that not only in my dissident
activity but in prison my best friends were

00:32:56.769 --> 00:33:04.240
people with strong identities. Why, because
in prison you-you-you can never know who is

00:33:04.240 --> 00:33:09.410
the real and who is not. Because KGB succeeded
to create it was to feel it among two hundred

00:33:09.410 --> 00:33:12.380
million people; nobody knows who is informer,
who is not.

00:33:12.380 --> 00:33:17.750
But in prison, where they -- KGB decide with
who you will be in one cell of course they

00:33:17.750 --> 00:33:20.830
can decide, you-you suspect everybody.

00:33:20.830 --> 00:33:31.159
And what you find out that the bet-best way
to-to-to know something about person if this

00:33:31.159 --> 00:33:38.820
person has strong identity of his or her own.
If this person has things for which he is

00:33:38.820 --> 00:33:40.220
ready to die for.

00:33:40.220 --> 00:33:46.720
My closest friend was religious, Christian
activist who was persecuted for-for teaching

00:33:46.720 --> 00:33:54.220
Christianity to-to-to the, he actually himself
was young, but for the young people.

00:33:54.220 --> 00:33:59.399
And in the prison, he was ready to die for
his views but not to cooperate with KGB.

00:33:59.399 --> 00:34:03.870
So you could know that because for you, there
are things which are more important than your

00:34:03.870 --> 00:34:08.810
physical survival and when they-they threatened
me with death sentence, you know that you

00:34:08.810 --> 00:34:12.540
really don't want to cooperate with them because
you want to remain free and you became free

00:34:12.540 --> 00:34:16.149
only when you found your own world.

00:34:16.149 --> 00:34:24.079
So the-the same is to other people. That's
why Pentecostals and Ukrainian Nationals and

00:34:24.079 --> 00:34:30.109
Armenian dissidents they were my best friends
because I knew that I can rely on them as

00:34:30.109 --> 00:34:32.149
they can rely on me.

00:34:32.149 --> 00:34:39.720
So this connection between freedom and identity
was very powerfully seen there.

00:34:39.720 --> 00:34:48.230
Now the free world, we could never survive
in our struggle in one day if from the very

00:34:48.230 --> 00:34:51.960
first day it didn't become the struggle of
all the Jews of the world and then also all

00:34:51.960 --> 00:34:53.090
the free people of the world.

00:34:53.090 --> 00:34:54.090
Because if we were organizing small demonstrations:
five people, for five minutes, standing in

00:34:54.090 --> 00:34:59.870
the Center of Moscow. Why, because you couldn't
have more than five people because then KGB

00:34:59.870 --> 00:35:03.880
will know at once and there'll be no demonstration.

00:35:03.880 --> 00:35:10.740
You couldn't, even if KGB does know in advance
it -- you cannot stand with a slogan, "Freedom

00:35:10.740 --> 00:35:22.060
to political prisoners," in the center of
Moscow more than five minutes be-before you're

00:35:22.060 --> 00:35:23.060
arrested.

00:35:23.060 --> 00:35:27.640
And then your partners, establish partnership
by years of prison and you get asked, "So

00:35:27.640 --> 00:35:33.780
what is the sense of this stupid demonstration
for five minutes of pleasure or standing in

00:35:33.780 --> 00:35:34.850
the center of Moscow, you're getting five
years of prison?"

00:35:34.850 --> 00:35:37.220
But the thing is that it was organized well;
that was one-one of my obligations. Meaning

00:35:37.220 --> 00:35:43.660
that at least one foreign journalist knows
in advance and he will come and he will inform;

00:35:43.660 --> 00:35:48.880
and there is no Internet, there was no CNN,
but in the evening on BBC or Voice of America,

00:35:48.880 --> 00:35:53.320
or Radio Liberty it will be broadcasted that
five Jews went on demonstration.

00:35:53.320 --> 00:35:57.970
Next day they'll be hundreds of thousands
of Jews who will go on demonstrations; really

00:35:57.970 --> 00:36:02.400
physically hundreds of thousands of Jews.
They will write to their senators and congressman;

00:36:02.400 --> 00:36:07.440
they'll demand from the State Department to
protest. The Soviet ambassadors will be called

00:36:07.440 --> 00:36:12.250
in down in street in-in Paris and in Washington,
demand.

00:36:12.250 --> 00:36:17.260
American legislators will pass, they pass
special legislation connecting freedom of

00:36:17.260 --> 00:36:22.070
immigration with all the trade interests of
the former Soviet Union.

00:36:22.070 --> 00:36:24.800
And that is how the struggle was built.

00:36:24.800 --> 00:36:31.320
KGB when we were there for a year and half
and they were interrogating me and threatening

00:36:31.320 --> 00:36:37.520
me and so they were saying, "What are you
building your hopes on? Look who you're supporting

00:36:37.520 --> 00:36:39.510
you; they are a bunch of students and housewives.
And we are KGB."

00:36:39.510 --> 00:36:42.420
And they-they give good, great, gave great
definition about it. Nine years later when

00:36:42.420 --> 00:36:47.710
I was released I went from one community to
the other to thank you, the army of students

00:36:47.710 --> 00:36:52.380
and housewives because for 20 years this army
of students and housewives was fighting and

00:36:52.380 --> 00:37:00.329
didn't let Soviet Union even one day of peace.
And they mobilized, of course, all the leaders

00:37:00.329 --> 00:37:01.329
of the world.

00:37:01.329 --> 00:37:05.820
And they were Father Drinan, too young to-to
remember there was such member of K'nesset,

00:37:05.820 --> 00:37:13.830
member of, congressman in America, Christian,
Catholic, Father Drinan who left -- the Pope

00:37:13.830 --> 00:37:18.460
demanded for him to resign because he said
the that Catholic leader cannot be member

00:37:18.460 --> 00:37:21.369
of congress so unfortunately he left, he resigned.

