00:43:35.880 --> 00:43:41.770
It's true that it was a long and difficult
way and I think if in the beginning before

00:43:41.770 --> 00:43:48.329
I made my first step somebody would tell me,
"That if you'll do it, you'll go to prison

00:43:48.329 --> 00:43:52.550
and you can be sentenced to death. You'll
be accused in high treason and you will be

00:43:52.550 --> 00:43:56.880
405 days in the punishment cell, and you will
be five years in solitary confinement, and

00:43:56.880 --> 00:44:01.140
you'll be this, this, this" probably then
I would not do it. Probably, I don't know.

00:44:01.140 --> 00:44:02.140
[laughter]

00:44:02.140 --> 00:44:05.510
But it's doesn't go this way. It goes step
by step.

00:44:05.510 --> 00:44:12.450
First, you feel yourself enslaved. Then you
discover the power of identity, and it gives

00:44:12.450 --> 00:44:18.180
you a lot of big desire to belong to this
history and to these people. Then you discover

00:44:18.180 --> 00:44:22.589
the power of freedom. You start saying your
mind; speaking your mind.

00:44:22.589 --> 00:44:27.040
And it is such a powerful state of mind; you-you
really don't want to go back.

00:44:27.040 --> 00:44:32.710
And then you're becoming part of the struggle
which becomes very important. And you really

00:44:32.710 --> 00:44:36.730
feel yourself part of some important historical
struggle.

00:44:36.730 --> 00:44:42.990
And then in prison, where they start proposing
you different types of compromises: big compromises

00:44:42.990 --> 00:44:49.990
and small compromises. And you know you're,
the moment you start making their compromises,

00:44:49.990 --> 00:44:53.960
you will lose this freedom. You really feel
yourself even in prison, you feel yourself

00:44:53.960 --> 00:44:56.740
free person and there you are slave. You don't
want to go back.

00:44:56.740 --> 00:45:02.010
And that of course then there is a question
of how you keep it every day. For example,

00:45:02.010 --> 00:45:07.390
especially I was 405 days in punishment cell.
Punishment cell, by their law, you're not

00:45:07.390 --> 00:45:12.329
supposed to be more than 15 days because you
can become crazy. It's very cold, very dark,

00:45:12.329 --> 00:45:17.940
three pieces of bread, three cups of water,
nobody to talk to. You are supposed to become

00:45:17.940 --> 00:45:18.940
crazy simply.

00:45:18.940 --> 00:45:24.550
And officially it is to no more than 15 days.
I was kept 405 days there.

00:45:24.550 --> 00:45:30.069
So first of all, every day you have to remind
yourself how important you are; that it, that

00:45:30.069 --> 00:45:34.359
it, that you are part of that great history
and one word of you can influence and everything.

00:45:34.359 --> 00:45:39.290
They tried to convince me that there was Galileo
Galilei such a great scientist and he cooperated

00:45:39.290 --> 00:45:44.060
with inquisition. So who you are not to do
it? Be clear – it was Galilei.

00:45:44.060 --> 00:45:50.260
And I was thinking, "If Galileo Galilei cooperated
with inquisition and 400 years after this

00:45:50.260 --> 00:45:55.329
they are using it, the inquisition, using
it against me, so if I'll make any compromise

00:45:55.329 --> 00:45:59.170
for them 400 years after this, somebody will
be using it." That's how we think.

00:45:59.170 --> 00:46:01.980
So first of all you have to self-aggrandize
yourself.

00:46:01.980 --> 00:46:02.980
[laughter]

00:46:02.980 --> 00:46:08.349
On the other hand, you have to understand
that nothing is serious. You have to be able,

00:46:08.349 --> 00:46:13.930
to be able to laugh at everything. And it's
such an idiotic organization, this KGB.

00:46:13.930 --> 00:46:18.990
And it is so easy to make laugh of them and
you're making all this jovial, you're telling

00:46:18.990 --> 00:46:21.369
to these KGB people anti-Soviet jokes. There
was a lot of anti-Soviet jokes which of course

00:46:21.369 --> 00:46:22.710
we were told one, one.

00:46:22.710 --> 00:46:28.921
And here telling them some joke about Brezhnev
and it's so funny that you, you speak and

00:46:28.921 --> 00:46:33.330
you laugh. And you see that they are almost
exploding from desire to laugh but they cannot

00:46:33.330 --> 00:46:34.380
laugh. They will lose their job –

00:46:34.380 --> 00:46:35.380
[laughter]

00:46:35.380 --> 00:46:36.380
one place or the other.

00:46:36.380 --> 00:46:40.500
And I tell them, "And you want to say that
I'm in prison. You cannot even laugh when

00:46:40.500 --> 00:46:43.140
you want to laugh. And you want me to be like
you."

00:46:43.140 --> 00:46:45.510
So you're laughing while all of this [ ].

00:46:45.510 --> 00:46:52.869
The third thing is you have to use your brains.
As I said, I had great hobby, chess; absolutely

00:46:52.869 --> 00:46:59.349
great. I at the age of 12 I thought I'll be
world champion and then at 14 I understood

00:46:59.349 --> 00:47:09.170
I cannot be such a [ ], number one and number
two I was not interested so I went to look

00:47:09.170 --> 00:47:10.470
where I can be number one and it was prison.

00:47:10.470 --> 00:47:11.470
So –

00:47:11.470 --> 00:47:12.470
[laughter]

00:47:12.470 --> 00:47:22.300
so, but I was playing single ten years games
and went and so I didn't know for what I am

00:47:22.300 --> 00:47:23.300
doing it.

00:47:23.300 --> 00:47:28.820
In prison it became sense. In punishment cell
I played thousands of games in my head. I

00:47:28.820 --> 00:47:29.820
won all of them.

00:47:29.820 --> 00:47:30.820
[laughter]

00:47:30.820 --> 00:47:31.820
I, each game next day I'm improving the previous
result because then they black horse so now

00:47:31.820 --> 00:47:37.750
I'll play this option for the black and I
improve it and so instead of being degr-degradating

00:47:37.750 --> 00:47:38.750
intellectually I becoming better and better.

00:47:38.750 --> 00:47:46.329
And the final, most important thing my great
other hobby was singing. And I enjoyed singing,

00:47:46.329 --> 00:47:51.100
but the moment I start singing in the Kindergarten
the nanny says, "And you wait, you will sing

00:47:51.100 --> 00:47:55.000
after." Because people really didn't like
what I was singing; I was destroying every

00:47:55.000 --> 00:47:59.510
one melody. And they tried in school and summer
camp and everywhere people say, "No, please

00:47:59.510 --> 00:48:00.510
don't, don't, don’t."

00:48:00.510 --> 00:48:01.510
[laughter]

00:48:01.510 --> 00:48:05.510
So finally in the punishment cell I understood
that is the moment which nanny promised that

00:48:05.510 --> 00:48:06.910
you will sing light.

00:48:06.910 --> 00:48:07.910
[laughter]

00:48:07.910 --> 00:48:13.080
So in political prison where must be silence
like in grave because you are not supposed

00:48:13.080 --> 00:48:18.070
to say, you are not supposed to know what's
happening, who else is in prison.

00:48:18.070 --> 00:48:23.340
So I say here, "I have nothing to lose. I'm
already 400 days in punishment cell; five

00:48:23.340 --> 00:48:24.579
years in solitary confinement."

00:48:24.579 --> 00:48:29.839
I sing with all the power of my lungs something
very Zionist, very good. And they become crazy.

00:48:29.839 --> 00:48:35.540
First of all they don't understand what I'm
saying in Hebrew. And second they don't enjoy

00:48:35.540 --> 00:48:36.540
my singing.

00:48:36.540 --> 00:48:37.540
[laughter]

00:48:37.540 --> 00:48:44.190
And so it-it's such a pleasure. And so that's
how I sang for nine years, okay?

00:48:44.190 --> 00:48:45.190
[laughter]

00:48:45.190 --> 00:48:46.190
[pause]

00:48:46.190 --> 00:48:47.190
