00:50:17.550 --> 00:50:22.859
At some moment in prison already I was for
few years in prison, and I was on the long

00:50:22.859 --> 00:50:28.200
hunger strike, hunger strike which continued
110 days where they were not letting me write

00:50:28.200 --> 00:50:29.760
letters and then they gave up.

00:50:29.760 --> 00:50:34.300
There was big pressure all over the world:
President Reagan, Margaret Thatcher, Mitterand;

00:50:34.300 --> 00:50:38.849
everybody was demanding from Soviet Union
to release me.

00:50:38.849 --> 00:50:43.410
And finally they gave up and let me write
letters. And they denies me the meeting with

00:50:43.410 --> 00:50:51.710
my mother and I had, in nine years I had two
meeting. And she tells me later on that it

00:50:51.710 --> 00:50:56.920
was the end of Madrid Conference, Madrid Conference
was a continuation of Helsinki process, and

00:50:56.920 --> 00:51:05.090
there Americans put a condition that they
will not sign this agreement without my release.

00:51:05.090 --> 00:51:11.911
And the Russians agreed that if I will sign
the letter they will write that because I

00:51:11.911 --> 00:51:20.809
have, I am in bad health after hunger strike
and they asked Soviet Union to show human-humanism

00:51:20.809 --> 00:51:23.079
and to release me, I will be released.

00:51:23.079 --> 00:51:26.330
And Americans were in rapture; American two
leaders that were American delegation and

00:51:26.330 --> 00:51:32.410
I don't want to mention their names, they
are very respectable and good people. They-they

00:51:32.410 --> 00:51:38.000
rushed to my wife who was leading campaign
for my release and they said that they got

00:51:38.000 --> 00:51:40.589
great agreement. Russians don't demand for
me to-to say that-that I'm criminal, don't

00:51:40.589 --> 00:51:48.990
demand to me that they are right or wrong.
They only ask be human, I am a poor ill Jew,

00:51:48.990 --> 00:51:53.340
release me please. And I will be released.

00:51:53.340 --> 00:51:54.660
And they thought it big victory.

00:51:54.660 --> 00:51:58.520
I will tell my wife, "Tell them it's bull.
There is no chance that my husband will do

00:51:58.520 --> 00:51:59.520
it."

00:51:59.520 --> 00:52:05.609
They were so furious. They said, "We reached
such an agreement so you have to do everything

00:52:05.609 --> 00:52:07.270
to convince them, him."

00:52:07.270 --> 00:52:14.040
Well my mother comes to the, they give her
special meeting in order she will tell me

00:52:14.040 --> 00:52:15.040
conditions.

00:52:15.040 --> 00:52:19.670
And she said, "that some dissidents think
that you can do it." I said, "I'm sure that

00:52:19.670 --> 00:52:25.990
my wife didn't say it." Mother said, "No,
my wife, your wi, Avital said that she leaves

00:52:25.990 --> 00:52:26.990
it to you."

00:52:26.990 --> 00:52:29.920
And then mother said what was-was very difficult
for her. She was 75 years old; she was a big

00:52:29.920 --> 00:52:33.920
fighter; she wanted me very much to be out
and she said, "And I am not telling you what

00:52:33.920 --> 00:52:39.609
to do. We leave it to you." And I said, "I
don't have even to think for a moment. There

00:52:39.609 --> 00:52:45.910
is no way that I'll sign it. There is no way
that I will give them any legitimacy to-to-to

00:52:45.910 --> 00:52:52.870
what they did. If they want to release me
they don't, they don't need my letters. But

00:52:52.870 --> 00:52:58.570
they want this letter in order to give some
kind of legitimacy to what they were doing."

00:52:58.570 --> 00:53:05.520
And so I have say to this day some American
officials believe that because of some radical

00:53:05.520 --> 00:53:11.990
views I betrayed them; President Reagan was
okay, he was okay. He continued his struggle.

00:53:11.990 --> 00:53:18.750
But I say that then, in this clear moment
of confrontation you really feel and see it

00:53:18.750 --> 00:53:26.700
very clearly that any moral compromise which
will give legitimacy to their right is strenthening

00:53:26.700 --> 00:53:32.420
them and weakening in fact all this time which
you had. After all these years that you already

00:53:32.420 --> 00:53:38.819
put it this moral plan so high and they had
such desperation they really feel themselves

00:53:38.819 --> 00:53:40.490
pressed; they cannot decrease the pressure.

00:53:40.490 --> 00:53:48.319
And I want to say that who knows if they decrease
the pressure then if our moral [ ] could be

00:53:48.319 --> 00:53:52.310
weakened, if the world would stop pressure
with Soviet Union; maybe Soviet Union would

00:53:52.310 --> 00:53:53.950
have exist until this day.

00:53:53.950 --> 00:54:01.290
But only because some moment is becomes uncompromised
moral struggle and Soviet Union then has to

00:54:01.290 --> 00:54:05.319
make some concessions that what they-they,
I was released, other political prisoners

00:54:05.319 --> 00:54:10.270
was released, and then the moment regime is,
has less control, it simply fell apart; exactly

00:54:10.270 --> 00:54:11.940
as are we are predicting.

00:54:11.940 --> 00:54:18.550
So I-I believe that at some moment when you're
dealing with evil, if you really want that

00:54:18.550 --> 00:54:24.180
this evil will disappear, you cannot make
a moral compromise with them.

00:54:24.180 --> 00:54:25.180
Thank you.

00:54:25.180 --> 00:54:26.180
[pause]

00:54:26.180 --> 00:54:32.230
&gt;&gt;female #2: Hi. Thank you again for coming
to speak to us today. It was a really interesting

00:54:32.230 --> 00:54:33.230
talk.

00:54:33.230 --> 00:54:38.829
And one of the points that you had mentioned
was about the story of identity and kind of

00:54:38.829 --> 00:54:43.911
freedom fighting and kind of wearing the dual
hats of both fighting for freedom for the

00:54:43.911 --> 00:54:47.500
Jewry as well as for universally.

00:54:47.500 --> 00:54:51.401
So I was curious you-you've been a member
of Parliament and Cabinet for a few years,

00:54:51.401 --> 00:54:59.369
kind of what is your outlook of the Palestinian
struggle for freedom? And how Israel is going

00:54:59.369 --> 00:55:01.010
to make that happen?

00:55:01.010 --> 00:55:04.660
&gt;&gt;Natan Sharansky: Well for this, you have
to read my second book,

00:55:04.660 --> 00:55:05.660
[laughter]

00:55:05.660 --> 00:55:06.910
"The Case for Democracy".

00:55:06.910 --> 00:55:10.589
But okay I'll tell you.

00:55:10.589 --> 00:55:11.589
[pause]

00:55:11.589 --> 00:55:16.700
I'm not big believer in the so called peace
process. The reason for this is very simple,

00:55:16.700 --> 00:55:21.819
because all the peace process, at least until
the-the very recent times, was absolutely

00:55:21.819 --> 00:55:27.170
disconnected from the question of democratic
reforms.

00:55:27.170 --> 00:55:34.010
As a result from the very beginning we were,
in '93, I don't know if you were born, but

00:55:34.010 --> 00:55:35.010
in '93 –

00:55:35.010 --> 00:55:36.010
[laughter]

00:55:36.010 --> 00:55:42.059
was-was-was signed, was signed Oslo Agreement.
And-and when we took Yasser Arafat who before

00:55:42.059 --> 00:55:48.790
this was world renowned terrorist and gave
him legitimacy it brought him to Palestine.

00:55:48.790 --> 00:55:55.339
And our Prime Minister then one week after
they sign an agreement said, "It is very good

00:55:55.339 --> 00:56:01.850
that Yasser Arafat is a dictator and not democrat.
Because as a dictator who is not restricted

00:56:01.850 --> 00:56:08.780
by human rights, Supreme Court, and heart
bleeding liberals," I quote, "he will fight

00:56:08.780 --> 00:56:12.049
Hamas much better than we can do it."

00:56:12.049 --> 00:56:16.970
That's when I wrote my first article against.
I wrote, "We will do everything to strengthen

00:56:16.970 --> 00:56:22.390
him as a dictator, and he is a dictator in
order to survive. We'll do everything that

00:56:22.390 --> 00:56:26.869
Palestinians will hate us because otherwise
he cannot really control his own people. And

00:56:26.869 --> 00:56:32.310
that it should be our interests that he will
be controlled by Supreme Court, by his Supreme

00:56:32.310 --> 00:56:37.750
Court, by his human rights organizations,
and by real heart bleeding liberals or free

00:56:37.750 --> 00:56:41.990
press whatever was of them."

00:56:41.990 --> 00:56:48.250
And well we know historically how, who won
in this battle; Arafat won; Hamas-Hamas won.

00:56:48.250 --> 00:56:55.970
And so I-I do have friend, first of all I
do believe in peace in Palestinian democratic

00:56:55.970 --> 00:57:03.500
state. I don't believe that our efforts, and
I said it to Clinton, I said it to Bush, I

00:57:03.500 --> 00:57:07.549
said it to all our governments, and I unfortunately
I was dissident of this.

00:57:07.549 --> 00:57:14.940
I said, "I don't believe that our attempts
to build peace with dictators ignoring the

00:57:14.940 --> 00:57:20.329
real needs of Palestinians can bring stability."

00:57:20.329 --> 00:57:26.170
And unfortunately each time when we were doing
this it happened to be right.

00:57:26.170 --> 00:57:32.150
Now I do have friends, Palestinians who are
real democrats. But each time when I was trying

00:57:32.150 --> 00:57:38.960
to bring them to the corridors of power in
Jerusalem, in Washington, or in Europe, the

00:57:38.960 --> 00:57:45.770
most difficult was in Europe, the answer also
always was, "But how much strength these people

00:57:45.770 --> 00:57:50.490
have? We have to deal with those who really
can control the situation. That's why we have

00:57:50.490 --> 00:57:54.840
to deal with Yasser Arafat. That's why we
have to deal with Abu Allan and Hamas and

00:57:54.840 --> 00:57:57.059
so on, because they have the real power."

00:57:57.059 --> 00:58:01.859
I can speak a lot about situation with human
rights, opposing authority or the rights of

00:58:01.859 --> 00:58:04.991
women. About the rights of gays, sometimes
I appear on campus with Palestinian gays and

00:58:04.991 --> 00:58:16.619
with some others who can tell you a lot about
the situation. I believe that as long as we

00:58:16.619 --> 00:58:21.380
are ignoring the real-real issues of freedom
of Palestinians, we are deceiving ourselves.

00:58:21.380 --> 00:58:30.770
And I'll tell you from my own experience not
only when you are a man [ ] but specifically

00:58:30.770 --> 00:58:35.640
Palestinians can be closer to democratic way
of life than maybe any other group of Muslims

00:58:35.640 --> 00:58:41.251
because they have been in Diaspora, because
they were involved in free economy, because

00:58:41.251 --> 00:58:48.119
through-through Israel, and because they are
so close to-to they can appreciate the real

00:58:48.119 --> 00:58:49.700
advantages of democracy.

00:58:49.700 --> 00:58:55.440
The fact that in the last 17 years we gave
so much power to dictators who are interested

00:58:55.440 --> 00:58:59.079
to destroy all this democracy is only weakening
chance for peace.

00:58:59.079 --> 00:59:02.431
But again that is my private opinion which
has nothing to do with my chairmanship of

00:59:02.431 --> 00:59:06.150
Jewish Agency.

00:59:06.150 --> 00:59:11.741
&gt;&gt;female #2: Thank you.

00:59:11.741 --> 00:59:12.741
[laughter]

00:59:12.741 --> 00:59:13.741
&gt;&gt;Natan Sharansky: Okay.

00:59:13.741 --> 00:59:14.741
[pause]

00:59:14.741 --> 00:59:15.741
&gt;&gt;commentator: It's time for one last question.

00:59:15.741 --> 00:59:16.741
&gt;&gt;male #2: How did you find out that you were
going to be released from the Soviet prison?

00:59:16.741 --> 00:59:25.100
&gt;&gt;Natan Sharansky: Ah. Well first of all things
that I didn't know; what I didn't know in

00:59:25.100 --> 00:59:32.839
19, in November of 1985 there was summit,
first summit between Reagan and Gorbachev

00:59:32.839 --> 00:59:34.380
in Geneva.

00:59:34.380 --> 00:59:41.059
And of course my wife, as all these years,
she came there and demonstrated in front of,

00:59:41.059 --> 00:59:50.049
together with some students and housewives
from-from New York, from Toronto, from Paris,

00:59:50.049 --> 00:59:52.299
who came and demonstrated with her.

00:59:52.299 --> 00:59:55.940
And she was demonstrating, she was in the
uniform of the prisoner or as the westerners

00:59:55.940 --> 01:00:03.799
think that that of the uniform of the prisoner,
it doesn't matter -- it was.

01:00:03.799 --> 01:00:08.549
And President Reagan as he later told me,
President Reagan, when Gorbachev started telling

01:00:08.549 --> 01:00:14.200
him, "Let us speak about real issues why you
again you're speaking about all this bunch

01:00:14.200 --> 01:00:20.920
of criminals, who they represent. They represent,
nobody exactly what we today say about dissidents.

01:00:20.920 --> 01:00:30.230
Reagan took him to the window and said, "You
see you-you know that I know that Sharansky

01:00:30.230 --> 01:00:34.960
is not American spy and you know. But you
know after all it doesn't matter," he said.

01:00:34.960 --> 01:00:42.540
"My people believe to that lady," he said.
"And as long as she is demonstrating, they

01:00:42.540 --> 01:00:49.170
will not trust you. So we-we really have to-to
start from this."

01:00:49.170 --> 01:00:51.460
I knew nothing about it.

01:00:51.460 --> 01:00:58.710
Three days after this I am in Siberia in punishment
cell again very weak lying on the floor, I

01:00:58.710 --> 01:01:01.000
don't have any strength to-to move.

01:01:01.000 --> 01:01:07.500
Suddenly they take me from this punishment
cell and move to the hospital. And they start,

01:01:07.500 --> 01:01:13.059
to the prison hospital. And they start feeding
me. And they feed me with things which I already

01:01:13.059 --> 01:01:17.470
forgot that they exist. When they brought
me eggs, I didn't understand what it is -- for

01:01:17.470 --> 01:01:21.980
nine years I didn't see eggs; and meat and
butter and milk, things which I didn't see

01:01:21.980 --> 01:01:25.750
these nine years.

01:01:25.750 --> 01:01:28.930
Well thank God at that moment I didn't know
that as a Jew I'm not supposed to eat butter

01:01:28.930 --> 01:01:29.930
 –

01:01:29.930 --> 01:01:30.930
[laughter]

01:01:30.930 --> 01:01:33.340
and bread or meat together so I ate everything-everything
what they brought me I ate, ate, ate.

01:01:33.340 --> 01:01:38.770
One of these days they started giving me injections
of glucose and some special vitamins which

01:01:38.770 --> 01:01:46.800
they were injecting me in another and it gave
me a lot of strength. They gave me two hours

01:01:46.800 --> 01:01:52.900
of walk every day in the snow and the sun;
in Siberia for half a year I didn't see any

01:01:52.900 --> 01:01:53.900
sun.

01:01:53.900 --> 01:01:57.420
And suddenly I start feeling a bit myself
stronger and stronger. I could walk, I could

01:01:57.420 --> 01:02:03.750
make exercise. I added 15 kilos, now I added
another 20 kilos –

01:02:03.750 --> 01:02:04.750
[laughter]

01:02:04.750 --> 01:02:11.320
Suddenly, and I was sure that they were preparing
me for another meeting with some KGB leader

01:02:11.320 --> 01:02:13.930
from time to time they wanted to do that.

01:02:13.930 --> 01:02:20.299
Suddenly well I will not go into details you
can read it in my books but at that moment

01:02:20.299 --> 01:02:31.271
they take me from the prison, change my clothes,
put me in the car, take a few hours to the

01:02:31.271 --> 01:02:38.569
airport in [ ], and then put me in the airplane.
And huge airplane, 200 seats, only I and four

01:02:38.569 --> 01:02:39.569
KGB –

01:02:39.569 --> 01:02:40.569
[laughter]

01:02:40.569 --> 01:02:44.970
people like in good old days when they were
following me day and night were there for

01:02:44.970 --> 01:02:45.970
me and we are flying.

01:02:45.970 --> 01:02:48.010
They don't say where.

01:02:48.010 --> 01:02:54.140
By sun I see that we go to the West. And so
after some hours it's clear that Soviet Union

01:02:54.140 --> 01:03:01.580
is a huge country that also has its [ ]. They
inform me officially in solemn voice that

01:03:01.580 --> 01:03:08.809
there is a special decision of Soviet Government
for my bad behavior on behalf Soviet citizenship

01:03:08.809 --> 01:03:10.290
I am deprived of Soviet citizenship –

01:03:10.290 --> 01:03:11.290
[laughter]

01:03:11.290 --> 01:03:12.290
and exiled from Soviet too.

01:03:12.290 --> 01:03:13.290
[laughter]

01:03:13.290 --> 01:03:21.990
So then I tell them it's such a solemn moment,
I say, "I want to make a statement." They

01:03:21.990 --> 01:03:26.099
say, "Oh no, you don't say it, it's enough
you've just spoken up."

01:03:26.099 --> 01:03:27.099
[laughter]

01:03:27.099 --> 01:03:28.609
But I feel that such a great audience - four
KGB men -- I had to something to say. And

01:03:28.609 --> 01:03:36.200
I insist and I say that, "I declare now that
I never was American spy, but I was fighting

01:03:36.200 --> 01:03:42.869
for freedom and I hope and I'm sure the day
will come when all 200 million Soviet people

01:03:42.869 --> 01:03:44.520
will get freedom as I get it today."

01:03:44.520 --> 01:03:48.160
And I say it. I felt it's very important for
me to-to say this. [laughs]

01:03:48.160 --> 01:03:49.160
[laughter]

01:03:49.160 --> 01:03:51.171
I don't know why it was important for me to
say to them that I'm not American spy, but

01:03:51.171 --> 01:03:52.589
it was such an important moment.

01:03:52.589 --> 01:03:58.369
And then we landed and I all time looked at
now I will see my wife. And then I see there

01:03:58.369 --> 01:04:02.490
is DDR. DDR is German Democratic Republic,
it doesn't exist today. I say, "Oh my God."

01:04:02.490 --> 01:04:07.410
Then I will not see her because German Democratic
Republic.

01:04:07.410 --> 01:04:14.700
And they tell me, "You see there the car.
We don't --" there is a lot of journalists,

01:04:14.700 --> 01:04:22.260
cameras and they say, "We-we don't want to
go out now you will be soon free. You go straight

01:04:22.260 --> 01:04:24.490
to that car. Agreed?"

01:04:24.490 --> 01:04:26.170
And the moment he said, "Agreed," I said,
"What do you mean, agreed? All these years

01:04:26.170 --> 01:04:31.329
I never agreed with you. You tell me to go
straight I'll go zig-zag so."

01:04:31.329 --> 01:04:32.329
[laughter]

01:04:32.329 --> 01:04:38.140
So they said, well because it was really very
important not to give up on anything to them.

01:04:38.140 --> 01:04:44.730
So they say, "Okay." Then, so they went on
two sides to the car and I, as promised, went

01:04:44.730 --> 01:04:50.010
zig zag to the car, but shortly speaking,
they took me on the Glienicke Bridge between

01:04:50.010 --> 01:04:54.150
Eastern Berlin and Western Berlin which don't
exist today -- between Eastern Germany and

01:04:54.150 --> 01:04:55.920
Western Germany -- it doesn't exist today.

01:04:55.920 --> 01:05:01.760
Between the world of Communism that doesn't
exist today and the world of freedom.

01:05:01.760 --> 01:05:08.210
And there American Ambassador took me through
over the bridge and then I said, "Where is

01:05:08.210 --> 01:05:10.020
the border?" He said, "This line is the border."

01:05:10.020 --> 01:05:16.471
I-I – And I forgot to say they gave me few
clothes and all it was very big on me as you

01:05:16.471 --> 01:05:23.690
can understand. But they didn't give me the
belt because of course prisoners are not supposed

01:05:23.690 --> 01:05:28.160
to have belt. So they gave me some rope which
was keeping my pants. So when they said, "There

01:05:28.160 --> 01:05:31.900
is the border," I jumped over it. And the
rope broke.

01:05:31.900 --> 01:05:32.900
[laughter]

01:05:32.900 --> 01:05:37.900
And I get there and each hour they ask, "What
was your first thought when you entered freedom?"

01:05:37.900 --> 01:05:39.660
I said, "How not to lose my pants."

01:05:39.660 --> 01:05:40.660
[laughter]

01:05:40.660 --> 01:05:40.661
[applause]

